You see that bag of frozen peas? Make pesto. At the link in bio, Zola Gregory (@zolagregory) shares a recipe that gives frozen vegetables their main character moment.⁠
⁠
📸: @elilu.jpg

How does a venture capitalist working in and around food actually grocery shop? Elly Truesdell (@ellytruesdell), founder and managing partner of New Fare Partners, joins us on the show today to tell us all about it.⁠
⁠
Illustration by @skrzat

Dressed eggs can vary from phoned-in (salt and vinegar potato chip crumbs and minced windowsill chives) to borderline brilliant (a sprinkle of spicy mentaiko, toasted bread crumbs, and thinly sliced scallions). At the link in bio, Anna Hezel (@ahezel) shares some inspiration.⁠
⁠
📸: Christopher Hirsheimer

Today on the podcast is Gail Simmons (@gailsimmonseats)—while many know her best from Top Chef, Gail’s career in food expands way beyond a judge’s table. Link in bio to listen!⁠
